SAINT PAUL MERCURY INDEMNITY COMPANY OF SAINT PAUL, a Corporation, v. Frank O’BRIEN et al., as Members of the Kansas Commission of Labor and Industry, et al. No. 1695. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. Oct. 24, 1938. Brooks, Fleeson. & Aley, of Wichita, Kan., for appellant. Clarence V, Beck, Atty. Gen.; of Kansas, and Matson, Stearns & Villepigue, of Wichita, Kan. for appellees.

Before LEWIS and PHILLIPS, Circuit. Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed on motion of appellant at appellant’s costs.
